### Section Structure
<section data-section-type="activity_fill_in_the_blank" data-section-id="SECTION_ID_FROM_INPUT" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">

### Activity Components

**1. Instructions**
- Use FontAwesome icons: `<i class="fas fa-book text-blue-700 mr-2"></i>` for reading, `<i class="fas fa-pen-to-square text-blue-700 mr-2"></i>` for writing
- Text in `<span>` with data-id
- Class: `text-center mb-2` or `text-center mb-4`
- Can include optional link buttons with purple styling

**2. Fill-in-the-Blank Sentences (PREFERRED — Inline Blanks)**

This is the **default and strongly preferred** layout. Each sentence containing a blank is wrapped in a container with the `fitb-sentence` class. Instead of placing `<input>` elements directly, insert `[[blank:item-N]]` placeholder markers at the exact position where the missing word belongs.

Rules for `[[blank:item-N]]` markers:
- `N` is the sequential item number (1, 2, 3, ...)
- Place the marker **exactly where the missing word goes** in the sentence
- The marker replaces the missing word — do NOT leave the original word in the text
- Markers are placed inside elements that have a `data-id` attribute
- At runtime, JavaScript will replace these markers with interactive `<input>` elements
- **Hint/placeholder text**: If the input text contains `[placeholder:word]` markers (e.g., `[placeholder:afloja]`), these indicate the textbook showed the answer as a visible hint in the blank. Convert each one to `[[blank:item-N:word]]` — for example, `[placeholder:afloja]` becomes `[[blank:item-3:afloja]]`. The hint appears as gray placeholder text inside the input field. You may also use `[[blank:item-N:hint]]` when the textbook visibly shows the answer or a hint even without a `[placeholder:]` marker (e.g., the word is dotted/underlined).

```html
<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <p class="fitb-sentence text-lg mb-3 leading-relaxed" data-id="text-2">
    El Sol es una [[blank:item-1]] que emite luz propia.
  </p>
  <p class="fitb-sentence text-lg mb-3 leading-relaxed" data-id="text-3">
    La Tierra gira alrededor del [[blank:item-2]].
  </p>
</div>
```

For numbered or labeled sentences, combine a label with the sentence:
```html
<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
    <p class="fitb-sentence text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <span class="font-semibold text-green-700 mr-2">1.</span>
      <span data-id="text-2">The process by which plants make food is called [[blank:item-1]].</span>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
    <p class="fitb-sentence text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <span class="font-semibold text-green-700 mr-2">2.</span>
      <span data-id="text-3">Plants need [[blank:item-2]] and water to grow.</span>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
```

**3. Hierarchical Diagram** (secondary layout — use only when the textbook explicitly shows a diagram/concept map):
```html
<div class="flex flex-col items-end gap-4 mb-6 md:w-3/5 mx-auto">
  <div class="bg-green-200 p-3 rounded-lg w-full">
    <label class="font-semibold" data-id="text-1">Main Title</label>
    <input class="w-full p-2 border border-gray-300 rounded"
           data-aria-id="aria-1-0-0"
           data-activity-item="item-1"
           tabindex="0"
           type="text" />
  </div>
  <div class="relative bg-blue-200 p-3 rounded-lg w-4/5">
    <div class="absolute right-full top-1/2 transform -translate-y-1/2 h-1 bg-blue-200 w-16 mr-1"></div>
    <div class="absolute right-full top-1/2 w-1 h-16 bg-blue-200" style="right: calc(100% + 64px); transform: translateY(-100%);"></div>
    <label class="font-semibold" data-id="text-2">Subtitle</label>
    <input class="w-full p-2 border border-gray-300 rounded"
           data-aria-id="aria-2-0-0"
